  title="Allergies and Indoor Air Quality"
  description="Allergies and indoor air quality: see how professional carpet cleaning helps improve the air your family breathes in Greater Montreal."
>
  <p>Did you know indoor air can be much more polluted than outdoor air? Your carpets play a major role in that balance.</p>

  <h2>The filter effect</h2>
  <p>Carpets act like a large filter, trapping dust, pollen, mold spores, and pet dander so they do not stay airborne all day.</p>

  <h2>Filters need to be cleaned</h2>
  <p>Like any filter, carpet fibers become saturated. Walking on dirty carpet releases particles back into the air, which is why periodic deep cleaning is recommended.</p>

  <h2>Our allergen-control approach</h2>
  <p>High-temperature extraction helps reduce dust mites and bacteria, improving indoor air quality and comfort for allergy-prone households.</p>
